Author: steve
Content: Yeah, I signed up for one of those sites where you pay them $50 to choose a name for you. Soon after, I discovered that those #$@#$ where just feeding me names from this! I refunded.

Author: steve
Content:
To demonstrate how absurd this concept really is, consider a similar idea: being able to transfer all user data between any multiplayer video game. How much of this data would really be useful in any given game? Just about none.

What the heck is the point! Without concrete examples, this argument is pretty empty.

Author: eastsidegringo
Title: Name Memorization Lesson from Flight of the Conchords
Content: I was watching this Flight of the Conchords clip where a guy named Brian bumps into a girl named Jenny, but can't remember her name (or anything about her) for the entire song. Never has nervous laughter been put to music more awkwardly or hilariously.\n

Author: kingnothing
Content: The only reason I ever rip streams is so I can have a nice assortment of music in a playlist that fits together.
